      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Version-controlled solver with documented test suite and traceable build process required at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2023 R1 is commercially validated; however, the hemolysis user-defined function (UDF) implementing the power-law damage model lacks a formal unit-test suite and version control history. Achieved level 2 only."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Method of manufactured solutions or equivalent analytical benchmark required for hemolysis transport equation at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Code verification was limited to standard lid-driven cavity and pipe-flow benchmarks available in the ANSYS verification manual. No manufactured solution was constructed for the power-law hemolysis transport equation. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Systematic grid convergence study with GCI below 5% for primary QoI required.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study completed; GCI for NIH below 4% at all operating points. Richardson extrapolation applied. Achieved level 3; falls short of level 4 due to absence of time-step refinement study for transient impeller passage effects."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must match COU operating envelope within documented tolerances; full uncertainty characterization of test rig boundary conditions required.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experiments were conducted at 37°C with bovine blood; COU specifies human blood at physiological hematocrit range. Temperature and fluid property differences introduce systematic bias not fully characterized. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative validation metric with statistical significance testing and coverage of all five COU operating points required.",
      "rationale": "MAPE of 18.3% observed across five operating points. No formal hypothesis test or validation metric with uncertainty bounds was applied. Comparison is qualitative-quantitative hybrid. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation QoI must directly correspond to the clinical decision QoI (absolute NIH) with no surrogate substitution.",
      "rationale": "Validation used NIH as the primary QoI consistent with the COU. However, spatial distribution of shear stress — a secondary QoI informing hotspot hemolysis — was not validated against experimental data. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry and operating conditions must be representative of the COU device geometry and clinical operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA generic pump geometry, which differs from the proprietary VAD impeller geometry in blade angle and tip clearance. Geometric similarity is partial. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Floating-point round-off and iterative solver tolerance effects on hemolysis QoI must be bounded.",
      "rationale": "Solver error analysis not performed. Iterative convergence was monitored via residual logs but no formal bound on solver-induced error in NIH was established. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented review of analyst setup choices including boundary condition assignment, turbulence model selection, and UDF parameterization.",
      "rationale": "No independent peer review of simulation setup was conducted. Single analyst performed all case setup and post-processing. Use error contribution unquantified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Sensitivity analysis on turbulence model and hemolysis damage model form required; alternative model forms must be evaluated.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected without comparative evaluation against RSM or LES. Power-law hemolysis exponents taken from Giersiepen 1990 without sensitivity study. Model form uncertainty not assessed."
    },
    {
